<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="187" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,151,176]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is in honor of the Argentinean arachnologist 
<taxonomicName authority="Scioscia" authorityName="Scioscia" box="[1057,1249,151,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Phalangiidae" genus="Cristina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cristina Scioscia</taxonomicName>
, who has helped in this study by sending material and illustrations made by Galiano.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="187" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,223,248]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Males of 
<taxonomicName box="[454,591,224,247]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Scopocira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sciosciae">
<emphasis box="[454,591,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">S. sciosciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName box="[889,1039,224,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Scopocira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscimana">
<emphasis box="[889,1039,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">S. fuscimana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the forked DEA, but can be distinguished by having the two DEA branches equally long (
<figureCitation box="[841,940,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 174 – 179. S" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1773,1796]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,551,1752]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,551,1752]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 174 – 179. S. pterodactyla sp. nov. 174 male, dorsal view; 175 left male palp, ventral view; 176 same, retrolateral view. S. sciosciae sp. nov. 177 male, dorsal view; 178 left male palp, ventral view; arrows point bifid dorsal embolic apophysis; 179 same, retrolateral view. Scale bar = 1 mm (174, 177); 0.25 mm (175 – 176, 178 – 179)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/249780/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">
Fig. 
<number box="[894,940,260,284]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" value="178.0">178</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption box="[151,1007,1632,1654]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/249781/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" targetBox="[151,1436,337,1610]" targetPageId="36">
